Alma is the perfect spot for a casual night out! The view is one of the best in the city, the food and drinks are good, and the service is friendly! Best of all, it won’t break the bank!  My girlfriend enjoyed a table on the heated rooftop where we ordered an array of food and drinks. We shared the chips and guac to start and it was really good - fresh, light, tasty. Next, we both ordered a bunch of tacos that were all really good. If I recall correctly, my favorite was the steak taco. I ended up having some Coronas and my girlfriend and I both had a bunch of their margs. I would highly recommend their margs, they’re tasty and strong! We ended with some churros, and they were good especially with the chocolate dipping sauce!  Our server was great. He knew the menu well, offered recommendations, and was quick to check up on us. No complaints.  As I mentioned before, the views are crazy good. Try and get a table close to the edge of the rooftop because they have the best views. Just trust me, you won’t be disappointed.

Well... Let's start with the good aspect---the service, cuisine, and ambiance is very good; they have three floors. Everyone seems to have been enjoying their food. The 1st and 2nd floors are well air conditioned but nothing to rave about. Now the bad... It's way too pricey for what you get... for example, I ordered an appetizer of salsa, guacamole with tortilla chips and 1 Modelo Negra beer... no draft beer available 😪... the price came out to around  $23.00 which includes the tip! Most, if not all of their main cuisines start at $19.00. It's just too expensive! Review the picture to review what I ordered. 🖖

One word- cockroaches. Ate outside on the roof the food and drinks were very good. However, mid meal my date pointed out a large bug right behind me. It was a large cockroach! We moved to another seat but as the dinner went on MULTIPLE cockroaches were seen coming out all over the upper deck. The waiter said it was "due to the summer months and we were eating outside so its expected"; casually waving it off. I understand eating outside with smaller bugs etc. but this was absolutely cringe-worthy and something from a management standpoint should NOT be in your restaurant no matter where you are sitting. 100% will never return, food was great but the idea of having cockroaches inches from you will ruin any meal.

Food and drinks are so good! This place has some of the best Mexican food and drink combination that I've tried. There's a rooftop eating area that I haven't been to yet but definitely plan to check out in the future. I'll have more to say on that in a future edit of this review. If you do decide to visit Alma you have to try the Alma Vita, one of their signature drinks. I say this with all honesty, it's probably the best mixed drink I've ever had. It uses a habanero infused tequila, mixes in some sour mix garnished with some candied ginger. The result, absolute perfection. Without making this a very long review I'll say the food was outstanding. Minus a star for the heavy price tag at the end of the night.
